  biggest  e ven intege r num ber that is in the ra nge  [x, y] in clusive. If
   there's no such number, then the functionshould return -1.

    For example:
    chooseNum(12, 15) = 14
    chooseNum(13, 12) = -1
     */
    public int chooseNum(int x, int y) {

canonical_solution:
        if (x > y) {
            return -1;
        }
        if (y % 2 == 0) {
            return y;
        }
        if (x == y) {
